 gas tokens can be burned to save on this deployment operation

devdoc.details: the gsve deployer has two purposes it deploys gsve smart wrappers, keeping track of the owners it allows users to deploy smart contracts using create and create2

GsveDeploy(bytes,address).details: deploys a smart contract using the create function if the contract is ownable, the contract ownership is passed to the message sender the gas token passed in as argument is burned by the moddifier

GsveDeploy2(uint256,bytes,address).details: deploys a smart contract using the create2 function and a user provided salt if the contract is ownable, the contract ownership is passed to the message sender the gas token passed in as argument is burned by the moddifier

GsveWrapperDeploy(address).details: deploys a gsve smart wrapper for the caller the ownership of the wrapper is transfered to the caller a note is made of where the users wrapper is deployed gas tokens can be burned to save on this deployment operation the gas tokens that the deployer supports are enabled in the wrapper before transfering ownership.

addGasToken(address,uint256).details: add support for trusted gas tokens - those we wrapped

compatibleGasToken(address).details: function to check if a gas token is supported by the deployer

deployedWalletAddressLocation(address).details: return the location of a users deployed wrapper

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
